    Class Description
    AbstractMessagingShard
    Prototype class for shards offering messaging functionality, containing some general implementation-independent methods.
    AbstractMessagingShard.MessagingDebug
    Debugging settings for messaging shards.
    AbstractNameBasedMessagingShard
    A simple extension of AbstractMessagingShard, which leaves to implement only AbstractMessagingShard.sendMessage(String, String, String) as an abstract method, and also the registration of a message receiver to the pylon.
    Agent
    Interface for agents.
    AgentEvent
    The class models an agent event, characterized by its type and, optionally, a set of parameters that have names.
    AgentEvent.AgentEventHandler
    The interface should be implemented by a class that can handle agent events for an agent component.
    AgentEvent.AgentEventType
    The enumeration specified the full set of agent-internal events that can occur.
    AgentEvent.AgentSequenceType
    The sequence type of an agent event specifies the order in which components should be notified of the event.
    AgentPingPong
    The implementation of the agents.
    AgentShard
    A shard (also called a component) is characterized by its functionality, identified by means of its designation -- an instance of AgentShardDesignation.
    AgentShardCore
    This class serves as base for the implementation of agent shards.
    AgentShardDesignation
    Implementation for shard designations.
    AgentShardDesignation.StandardAgentShard
    Enumeration of standard shard names / functionalities.
    AgentShardGeneral
    The class extends AgentShardCore and offers additional functionality for AgentShard implementations, especially in working together with other (known types of) shards.
    AgentWave
    The wave is a type of event that conveys information between two entities, whether these entities are agents, shards inside different agents, or shards inside the same agent.

    Simple implementation for Loader, which attempts to load the entity class by instantiating it: using a constructor that receives a MultiTreeMap as argument, or using the default constructor, and if the instance implements ConfigurableEntity, subsequently calling ConfigurableEntity.configure(net.xqhs.flash.core.util.MultiTreeMap).
